<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 This proposed rule would amend the Egg Research and Promotion Order to increase the assessment rate from 5 cents to
10 cents per 30-dozen case of commercial eggs. This proposal would also make a conforming amendment to regulations.
Notice also is hereby given that the Agricultural Marketing Service will conduct a referendum to determine whether
egg producers favor an increase in the assessment rate under the egg research and promotion program. Ballots and instructions
will be mailed directly to all known egg producers owning over 75,000 laying hens.



